25:
H-how long have you all been
standing there for?!
34: I suppose there's no hiding it now...
38: I think... I'm in love with Alk!
45: Then... What am I to do with myself?
54:
Ever since we returned from the
island, my heart has threatened to
leap out of my chest, and I've had
the most difficult time trying to
focus...
58:
This absolutely won't do! How am I
to get rid of these ailments?!
62: Ailments? I don't think you're sick.
67:
Aren't I, though? These feelings
weigh on me like a physical pain!
71:
I couldn't possibly marry Alk in the
state I'm in now!
76:
It, um, seems a little early to be
worrying about marriage, don't you
think?
80:
...Generally speaking, I believe
confessing helps most people,
regardless of whether their feelings
are reciprocated.
84:
I highly doubt my feelings would be
returned...
86:
Considering Alk is not in love with
me.
91:
If you are certain only rejection
awaits—
133:
I'm flattered, but... Sorry, I don't feel
the same way.
143:
Hmm... One moment, I need to
confirm something.
157:
But my heart is still pounding!
Rejection has done nothing to ease
my ailments!
162:
I'm sorry, but this is... a lot to take in. I
need a moment...
166:
Surely you have other ideas! Don't
you all have an abundance of
romantic experiences?
174:
I've spent most of my life dealing
with war...
180:
I have experienced rejection and
nothing else!
185:
So none of you are better off than
myself! I can't believe I trusted in
your wisdom!
189: My apologies for being of no help...
195:
S-Shirano, where are you when I
need youuuu!
201:
...Well, I believe I understand the gist
of the situation. I have a technique
that could help.
210:
Forcefully sealing something like
that away will only cause it to
become a curse.
213:
...Shywe, you only fall in love for the
first time once.
215:
Instead of forgetting your feelings
as fast as possible, why don't you
hold onto them? You never know
what the future might bring. One
day they could be reciprocated.
221:
Shirano, you always know exactly
what to say!
224:
Besides, your life will be much easier
if you love the person you intend to
marry.
226:
Your own happiness is a factor here
as well, you know.
235: I'm going to visit Alk one more time!
246: Alk! I... I don't want to give up after all!
250:
I've decided... I'll make you fall for me
one day, and then we'll get married!
255: I'm... pretty sure I rejected you earlier?
266:
It's just... I know what you're like. You'll
say what you feel, but you'd never
force someone to do something
they don't want.
269:
Which means I could still have a
chance... Unless I've read your
personality wrong?
274:
I guess if you want to keep trying, it's
your choice...
279:
This time, I'm doing this for my own
feelings. Not because of a prophecy.
281:
You best be prepared for my
renewed efforts!
289: Good luck. You're gonna need it.
